[Note]
❶prelude_clang problem
In my environment,"prelude_clang" was not downloaded after "repo".
If you are in the same situation,here is solution.

1.Go to this link.
  https://gitlab.com/jjpprrrr/prelude-clang/-/tree/master

2.Download the source code with "tar" file;zip file may fail.

3.Unzip with file manager.(file name is "prelude-clang-master")

4.Copy all files/folders in the "prelude-clang-master".

5.Go to "home/android/pe/prebuilts/clang/host/linux-x86" and make "clang-prelude" folder.

6.Copy the copied file to the "clang-prelude" folder.

7.Delete "<project name="jjpprrrr/prelude_clang" path="prebuilts/clang/host/linux-x86/clang-prelude" remote="gitlab" revision="master" />" from local_manifests.

❷FCM version problem
This device source code will probably produce this error.
"both device manifest and kernel release do not specify kernel FCM version"
Currently I do not have the technical ability to modify this source code, so I will modify it after downloading the source code with "repo".

1.Go to home/android/pe/device/xiaomi/beryllium/manifest.xml:1

2.change the code as follows
  <manifest version="1.0" type="device">
                   ⬇
  <manifest version="1.0" type="device" target-level="4">
